Merge pull request #15 from pensono/nothing-selected

logic to tell user to highlight text
added logic that lets the user know they need to highlight some text to use the extension. Doesn't just show blank "related to"

Merge pull request #14 from pensono/icons

removes "loading articles" when the articles populate the popup
Reorganize chrome extension into it's own folder
Change endpoint to something more senseable
Fix bug where some bing searches were returning no results
article shows up in paragraph format
updated with new sources, removed testing printing, corrected for url submission
removed old js code. Now, the article related to the highlighted text successfully shows up and is formatted

create Source to store name, reliability, and polarization. Create SourceDatabase to store multiple sources and access certain polarization and the most opposite (based on polarization). Example client (extract_polarization) creates sources and database and finds two sources most opposite.
moved css into its own file
highlight.js includes the POST ajax call passing in the highlighted text
